1
00:01:08,320 --> 00:01:10,120
<i>We were just two girls</i>
<i>finding out who we really were</i>

2
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:12,000
<i>and happened to cross paths. Nothing more.</i>

3
00:01:12,080 --> 00:01:13,360
And what about now?

4
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:16,040
<i>Now I've found the one I love the most.</i>

5
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:18,520
We decided to postpone Play Park's closure

6
00:01:18,600 --> 00:01:20,080
indefinitely.

7
00:01:20,160 --> 00:01:22,200
- Yeah!
- Yay!

8
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,640
Manager.

9
00:01:25,360 --> 00:01:26,880
<i>I've told you before</i>

10
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,160
that I don't care who you're close with.

11
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:32,040
<i>But if whoever or whatever</i>

12
00:01:32,120 --> 00:01:35,320
<i>stands in the way</i>
<i>of the life goal I've set for you,</i>

13
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:37,320
<i>I wouldn't let it go.</i>

14
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:59,480
I'm sorry.

15
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,120
I shouldn't have--

16
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:11,000
You went abroad for a meeting

17
00:05:12,200 --> 00:05:14,800
and didn't answer my calls.
That, I can understand.

18
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:17,880
But you left without even telling me.

19
00:05:18,520 --> 00:05:20,960
You even left my texts on read.

20
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,880
What was that supposed to mean?

21
00:05:25,760 --> 00:05:28,000
I wanted to try fading away for a while.

22
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,760
Ms. Lin.

23
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,720
I thought it might end quietly,

24
00:05:34,240 --> 00:05:36,200
but it didn't.

25
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:40,120
But why did it have to end?

26
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,120
Was it because

27
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:46,080
your father didn't want us to be together?

28
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:56,280
Jane said your father is very concerned
about the company’s work.

29
00:05:57,320 --> 00:05:58,800
Was it because of that?

30
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,160
You need to separate the issues.

31
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:06,160
It’s not that
Dad doesn’t like you personally,

32
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:10,400
he doesn't like anyone
who causes setbacks in my work.

33
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:14,520
He has high expectations for me.

34
00:06:16,760 --> 00:06:19,160
So you chose to leave me

35
00:06:20,800 --> 00:06:23,120
instead of working it out together?

36
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:31,320
Listen to me, okay?

37
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:35,400
I was so worried, you know?

38
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:38,960
I was afraid
you would get in trouble for dating me.

39
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:44,440
And don't you think
me being unable to eat or sleep

40
00:06:45,880 --> 00:06:47,560
was trouble enough?

41
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:50,960
I'm sorry.

42
00:06:53,160 --> 00:06:56,520
I needed to take a step back
to avoid conflict with Dad.

43
00:06:57,840 --> 00:07:01,760
I had to stop everything
before our relationship got worse.

44
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:07,520
I was afraid it would end up
like what happened with Prae.

45
00:07:13,560 --> 00:07:16,160
So I needed some time alone

46
00:07:16,760 --> 00:07:19,440
to process everything.

47
00:07:21,280 --> 00:07:22,760
Once I figured it out,

48
00:07:22,840 --> 00:07:25,320
I rushed back to you.

49
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:35,160
If we can prove to Dad

50
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:38,120
that our relationship helps us
support each other's careers,

51
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:42,400
maybe he won't stand in our way.

52
00:07:48,760 --> 00:07:50,520
I know it's not easy.

53
00:07:51,120 --> 00:07:52,720
We still have a lot to fight for.

54
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:57,000
Will you fight alongside me?

55
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:02,800
I just happen to be
a fighter who doesn’t back down.

56
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:10,280
Please don't walk away from me again.

57
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:14,240
If there's a next time,

58
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:16,760
I'll let you walk alone.

59
00:08:19,520 --> 00:08:20,800
I've learned my lesson.

60
00:08:38,880 --> 00:08:40,960
So that's why she turned off her phone.

61
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,240
Are you asleep, Gib?

62
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:50,760
Sorry. Can I ask you something?

63
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:53,160
Did anyone go to see Ms. Lin
at the house today?

64
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,320
Mm.

65
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,560
Ms. Lin, please be honest.

66
00:09:18,360 --> 00:09:21,680
Did you put off
Play Park's closing date indefinitely

67
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,440
because of me?

68
00:09:29,080 --> 00:09:30,920
I feel really bad

69
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:35,520
for causing trouble
between you and your father.

70
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,960
Don't blame yourself.

71
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:42,800
I didn't do it to please you.

72
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:47,560
But I really agree with your idea.

73
00:09:51,360 --> 00:09:52,640
What idea?

74
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:58,000
<i>I understand now</i>

75
00:09:58,640 --> 00:10:01,000
why you want to open a tutoring school.

76
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:05,200
It’s because
you attended those schools yourself

77
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:07,320
and became successful.

78
00:10:09,280 --> 00:10:10,800
You don't agree with the method?

79
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:14,440
It's not that I don't agree with it.

80
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,400
But…

81
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:19,360
I think if kids really have to study,

82
00:10:19,440 --> 00:10:21,040
they should be playing too.

83
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:24,560
It allows them
to grow and learn at the same time.

84
00:10:24,640 --> 00:10:26,680
It's better than attending
tutoring school every day.

85
00:10:26,760 --> 00:10:28,480
They’d be so stressed.

86
00:10:45,280 --> 00:10:46,800
I wasn't even being serious.

87
00:10:46,880 --> 00:10:49,280
I didn't expect you
to think so much about it.

88
00:10:52,600 --> 00:10:55,440
It hit so close to home.
How could I not think about it?

89
00:10:56,960 --> 00:11:00,520
I did try to capitalize
on what parents need.

90
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:04,600
I feel like a terrible person.

91
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:10,880
You're running a business.
Of course you look for profit.

92
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:12,840
Also,

93
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,880
you’re not just running

94
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,720
this tutoring school.

95
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:21,400
You're good at comforting people, huh?

96
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,760
I need to find a way

97
00:11:26,840 --> 00:11:29,640
to make the business model more seamless.

98
00:11:33,120 --> 00:11:35,440
Tell me if you need any help.

99
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:41,840
Just staying by my side like this
and not going anywhere is enough.

100
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,960
Lin. Lin.

101
00:13:13,960 --> 00:13:14,800
Dad.

102
00:13:18,520 --> 00:13:19,720
How was the meeting?

103
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,640
Let's talk about it at your house later.

104
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,080
IngIng, come on out.

105
00:13:53,440 --> 00:13:54,600
Hello.

106
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,120
Dad.

107
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:16,840
I've found my baking instructor.

108
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:35,640
IngIng is the manager at Play Park.

109
00:14:37,720 --> 00:14:39,040
So if Play Park shuts down,

110
00:14:39,120 --> 00:14:40,320
would you be out of work?

111
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,280
No, sir.

112
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:44,520
Mr. Pao has already found me another job.

113
00:14:46,040 --> 00:14:49,240
Play Park's customers love her
and trust her very much, Dad.

114
00:14:49,320 --> 00:14:52,120
If we get her to help us with PR,
it’ll be easier

115
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:54,520
for customers to apply for our courses.

116
00:14:58,680 --> 00:15:01,680
I’ll help Ms. Lin the best I can.

117
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:07,440
You did what I asked

118
00:15:07,520 --> 00:15:09,760
to buy yourself some time, didn't you?

119
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:15,280
Anyway, don't let the construction
be delayed for too long,

120
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:17,880
because the board
is watching your progress.

121
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:19,960
Yes, Dad.

122
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:26,320
Then let’s talk more at my house later.

123
00:15:27,840 --> 00:15:29,280
I’ll walk you out.

124
00:15:29,360 --> 00:15:31,440
It's okay. Stay with your friend.

125
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,280
Let's eat.

126
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:55,640
I've already cooked for you.

127
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:56,640
Let's go.

128
00:16:03,080 --> 00:16:04,360
CHANNEL 3 NEWS FAMILY

129
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:12,040
Manager, have you ever seen
the fugitive before?

130
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:13,160
I haven’t.

131
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:16,040
And no one on the staff knows him either.

132
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:17,280
Other than you,

133
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:19,680
was anyone injured?

134
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:20,880
No.

135
00:16:20,960 --> 00:16:23,640
Luckily, Play Park
wasn't open yet at that hour,

136
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,600
so there were no customers inside.

137
00:16:25,680 --> 00:16:27,840
<i>That was fortunate.</i>

138
00:16:27,920 --> 00:16:29,760
<i>Yes, we were very lucky.</i>

139
00:17:37,360 --> 00:17:38,480
May.

140
00:17:38,560 --> 00:17:39,800
RECHARGE STATION

141
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:41,160
Come on, come on.

142
00:17:49,560 --> 00:17:51,400
Okay, lift the left side a little.

143
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:54,040
That's it. Lock it in place.

144
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:56,040
I’ll go ahead and secure it, alright?

145
00:17:59,240 --> 00:18:00,080
Beautiful.

146
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:01,960
Perfect. Yay!

147
00:18:02,040 --> 00:18:03,880
- Yeah!
- Yay!

148
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:05,320
So beautiful.

149
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,520
Everyone, let's take group photos.

150
00:18:09,400 --> 00:18:11,480
- Yay!
- Yay!

151
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:24,080
So great.

152
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,200
Great job, guys.

153
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:28,560
- Fabulous.
- Well done.

154
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,840
Are you done?

155
00:18:36,920 --> 00:18:38,320
Is it too late to change my mind?

156
00:18:38,920 --> 00:18:40,600
Oh? Why are you changing your mind?

157
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:42,800
It doesn't really suit me.

158
00:18:42,880 --> 00:18:45,560
Come out and I’ll tell you
whether it suits you or not.

159
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:47,200
Don't laugh, okay?

160
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:49,080
Mm.

161
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:50,640
I'm covering my mouth.

162
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:06,720
You look cute.

163
00:19:06,800 --> 00:19:08,360
Don't I look funny?

164
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:09,320
Not at all.

165
00:19:09,400 --> 00:19:11,360
Kids love costumes like this.

166
00:19:11,960 --> 00:19:14,320
- I’m not doing it.
- No.

167
00:19:14,840 --> 00:19:15,960
It was your idea.

168
00:19:16,040 --> 00:19:17,560
You have to wear it. Let's go.

169
00:19:21,120 --> 00:19:22,840
- What's this?
- I'm calculating.

170
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,400
- Calculating right now.
- Really?

171
00:19:24,480 --> 00:19:26,280
Welcome. Right this way.

172
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:27,680
So what is it?

173
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:29,000
What's the number?

174
00:19:29,080 --> 00:19:29,920
Huh?

175
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:32,480
What's the number? No.

176
00:19:32,560 --> 00:19:34,520
I don't have enough fingers to count.

177
00:19:34,600 --> 00:19:35,480
Fingers?

178
00:19:35,560 --> 00:19:36,840
Then can you start from nine?

179
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:38,320
Nine, ten,

180
00:19:38,400 --> 00:19:39,240
eleven,

181
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:40,480
- twelve.
- Nine, ten.

182
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:41,760
Eleven, twelve.

183
00:19:41,840 --> 00:19:43,000
- What is this?
- Thirteen.

184
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:46,760
- You're so cool.
- Nine.

185
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:48,320
Hi.

186
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,640
Hi. Thank you.

187
00:19:49,720 --> 00:19:51,200
Thank you.

188
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:52,600
Okay, okay.

189
00:19:54,560 --> 00:19:57,040
- Here you go.
- Are you doing it again?

190
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:04,120
Is that right?

191
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:08,040
What about the other one?

192
00:20:08,120 --> 00:20:09,640
The one on the left.

193
00:20:09,720 --> 00:20:11,200
On the left?

194
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:13,040
- It's six.
- Oh, six?

195
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:15,680
This one? Yeah.

196
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:17,840
- Is that it?
- Is it right?

197
00:20:27,080 --> 00:20:29,360
A lot of parents
are interested in our booth.

198
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,680
Really?

199
00:20:31,200 --> 00:20:33,240
The kids were having a lot of fun too.

200
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:35,760
You're good. You've got the right idea.

201
00:20:36,560 --> 00:20:40,160
But the kids looked so happy.
They were all busy solving math problems.

202
00:20:40,680 --> 00:20:43,480
Some even came back to ask for the answers
and challenge each other.

203
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:45,960
- Yeah?
- They enjoyed it so much.

204
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:47,240
That's funny.

205
00:20:49,120 --> 00:20:52,280
Then can I get my commission upfront?

206
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:56,520
How about a trip to Pattaya instead?

207
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,120
I have a seminar there soon.

208
00:20:58,720 --> 00:20:59,920
Let me think about it.

209
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:03,800
Please?

210
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:05,440
Okay?

211
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:13,360
Mm.

212
00:21:23,480 --> 00:21:25,360
It's him! It's him!

213
00:21:25,440 --> 00:21:26,600
Sir.

214
00:21:27,280 --> 00:21:29,920
This lady told me
you were stalking her boss.

215
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:31,880
This is a misunderstanding.

216
00:21:31,960 --> 00:21:33,400
I don't even know her boss.

217
00:21:35,360 --> 00:21:37,160
Then show us what’s on your phone.

218
00:21:37,240 --> 00:21:38,760
I saw you filming my boss.

219
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:40,320
What? Who are you?

220
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:42,320
- What do you want from me?
- And who are you?

221
00:21:44,520 --> 00:21:45,920
I'm her ex-husband.

222
00:21:46,000 --> 00:21:48,200
Are you crazy?
My boss has never been married.

223
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:50,120
Is IngIng your boss?

224
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:52,800
Huh?

225
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:57,840
You're IngIng's husband?

226
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:58,880
Yeah.

227
00:22:05,200 --> 00:22:07,400
DROP-OFF POINT

228
00:22:17,240 --> 00:22:18,560
See you.

229
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:19,680
Bye-bye.

230
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,920
Ms. Lin, why didn't you wait for me?

231
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:24,840
Let’s go.

232
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:26,680
Uncle Somchai, open the door.

233
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:27,920
- Let's go.
- What’s going on?

234
00:22:28,000 --> 00:22:29,360
Let's leave. It's not safe here.

235
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:31,560
See you, Ing.

236
00:22:33,520 --> 00:22:34,600
Let's go.

237
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:45,800
Let's get moving.

238
00:23:16,200 --> 00:23:17,760
Tickle, tickle.

239
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:19,840
It tickles, right?

240
00:23:19,920 --> 00:23:20,880
Here.

241
00:23:20,960 --> 00:23:22,920
Whose crocodile is this?

242
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:26,560
Oh, it’s a seal. Whose seal is this?

243
00:23:29,680 --> 00:23:30,920
- Whoa.
- Wow.

244
00:23:33,600 --> 00:23:35,840
- Take a photo of us, Ith.
- Alright.

245
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:38,560
Look at the camera, Donut.

246
00:23:38,640 --> 00:23:40,720
- Look at the camera.
- One, two…

247
00:23:40,800 --> 00:23:41,800
Whoa.

248
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:42,840
Donut. Donut.

249
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,160
Yeah.

250
00:23:46,680 --> 00:23:47,720
One, two.

251
00:23:47,800 --> 00:23:49,200
- Does it look cute?
- So cute.

252
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:51,000
I mean Donut is so cute.

253
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:52,480
Yeah, I know.

254
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:54,400
Come here.

255
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:57,720
One, two, three.

256
00:23:57,800 --> 00:24:04,760
Three. Three. Three.

257
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:07,840
Three.

258
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:09,440
- Peekaboo!
- You want the seal?

259
00:24:09,520 --> 00:24:12,320
Whose son is this? So cute, right?

260
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,640
Right?

261
00:24:13,720 --> 00:24:16,360
Okay, the seal's here.
You like the seal, right?

262
00:24:19,680 --> 00:24:21,240
Come on. One, two…

263
00:24:24,440 --> 00:24:25,600
- One, two, three.
- What is it?

264
00:24:28,040 --> 00:24:29,040
Three.

265
00:24:41,880 --> 00:24:43,920
Ith, take Donut.

266
00:24:47,400 --> 00:24:48,480
- Come here.
- Go to Uncle Ith.

267
00:24:48,560 --> 00:24:50,240
Sit here with me, okay?

268
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:02,720
Stay with Uncle Ith, alright?
Stay with me.

269
00:25:06,120 --> 00:25:07,680
Long time no see.

270
00:25:08,440 --> 00:25:09,520
Why are you here?

271
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:11,920
Well, I missed my child.

272
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:13,360
I want to see his face.

273
00:25:15,800 --> 00:25:17,640
- Can I come inside?
- No.

274
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:19,920
You're not welcome here.

275
00:25:20,920 --> 00:25:21,880
Why are you here?

276
00:25:22,400 --> 00:25:23,720
Donut.

277
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:24,920
Wow.

278
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,560
My son is this big now?

279
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:27,680
Donut, come here.

280
00:25:28,320 --> 00:25:30,480
Let's go inside, okay?

281
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:34,960
Get out.

282
00:25:37,200 --> 00:25:39,000
Before I call the police.

283
00:25:39,080 --> 00:25:40,680
Do I have to listen to you?

284
00:25:59,360 --> 00:26:01,040
Why are you only telling me this now?

285
00:26:02,200 --> 00:26:05,120
If I’d told you earlier,
you wouldn’t have wanted to come home.

286
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:07,200
I still can't get over

287
00:26:07,280 --> 00:26:08,800
that fugitive pointing a gun at you.

288
00:26:08,880 --> 00:26:10,520
Your safety has to come first.

289
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:13,360
And did he say why he was stalking IngIng?

290
00:26:14,480 --> 00:26:17,240
He only said he thought
she might be his ex-wife,

291
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:19,200
so he came to see for himself.

292
00:26:19,280 --> 00:26:21,520
But I don't buy it, Ms. Lin.

293
00:26:21,600 --> 00:26:23,640
I think it's possible
they're still together

294
00:26:23,720 --> 00:26:25,040
and trying to trick you.

295
00:26:25,640 --> 00:26:28,360
That's impossible.
Ing would never lie to me.

296
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:30,280
You never know, Ms. Lin.

297
00:26:30,360 --> 00:26:32,000
Appearances can be misleading.

298
00:26:32,080 --> 00:26:34,600
And the two of you
haven’t known each other

299
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:35,960
that long, right?

300
00:26:54,480 --> 00:26:56,560
LILIN

301
00:27:12,320 --> 00:27:14,520
Donut, don’t be afraid, okay?

302
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:15,960
No need to be scared.

303
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:17,680
I'm right here.

304
00:27:17,760 --> 00:27:19,680
I'm right here, alright?

305
00:27:20,560 --> 00:27:21,760
IngIng.

306
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:28,040
Where are you two hiding?

307
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:34,400
Why are you scared of me?

308
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:35,880
I just missed my son

309
00:27:35,960 --> 00:27:36,960
and wanted to see him.

310
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:39,600
Come out.

311
00:27:39,680 --> 00:27:41,400
Let's talk nicely.

312
00:27:46,840 --> 00:27:48,080
IngIng.

313
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:50,480
Are you playing hide-and-seek with me?

314
00:27:54,400 --> 00:27:55,440
Good.

315
00:27:56,160 --> 00:27:57,920
Then hide properly.

316
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,600
Because Daddy’s coming to find you.

317
00:28:06,920 --> 00:28:07,800
LILIN
MISSED CALL

318
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:09,800
Ing's not answering her phone.

319
00:28:10,480 --> 00:28:12,160
She might be taking care of her child.

320
00:28:14,080 --> 00:28:15,400
I have a bad feeling about this.

321
00:28:16,800 --> 00:28:18,280
Ms. Lin, where are you going?

322
00:28:18,360 --> 00:28:21,040
Ms. Lin, please wait for me.

323
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:27,240
Are you in here?

324
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:30,040
Aha!

325
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:34,400
Not here.

326
00:28:40,400 --> 00:28:42,440
Or is it…

327
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:46,000
this room?

328
00:28:53,640 --> 00:28:55,400
Not here either.

329
00:28:56,960 --> 00:28:58,720
So it must be…

330
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:08,640
Find somewhere good to hide.

331
00:29:09,960 --> 00:29:12,160
Daddy's right at the door.

332
00:29:15,440 --> 00:29:16,880
Peekaboo!

333
00:29:28,800 --> 00:29:29,920
IngIng.

334
00:29:30,480 --> 00:29:31,920
Why are you hiding?

335
00:29:32,680 --> 00:29:33,840
Just come out and talk.

336
00:29:33,920 --> 00:29:36,040
I just missed him and wanted to see him.

337
00:29:43,720 --> 00:29:44,760
No need to be afraid.

338
00:29:44,840 --> 00:29:46,480
I won’t do anything to either of you.

339
00:29:54,800 --> 00:29:55,880
IngIng.

340
00:29:57,440 --> 00:29:58,720
IngIng, come out.

341
00:30:00,040 --> 00:30:03,240
- Don't be afraid.
- Open the door for me, IngIng.

342
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:06,560
IngIng.

343
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:08,560
Ing!

344
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:10,000
I said come out!

345
00:30:18,600 --> 00:30:20,120
Let's talk out here.

346
00:30:21,040 --> 00:30:21,920
Okay?

347
00:30:25,520 --> 00:30:27,280
Or do I need to break in?

348
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:32,320
IngIng, I'm calling your name
for the last time.

349
00:30:33,120 --> 00:30:34,800
If you still won't open the door,

350
00:30:34,880 --> 00:30:36,000
this is your last chance.

351
00:30:38,560 --> 00:30:39,800
IngIng!

352
00:30:39,880 --> 00:30:41,040
Damn it!

353
00:30:41,560 --> 00:30:42,640
Open the door!

354
00:30:43,480 --> 00:30:44,920
I said open the door!

355
00:30:49,240 --> 00:30:50,920
Ugh! Let go of me!

356
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:56,200
IngIng.

357
00:31:03,160 --> 00:31:04,160
Come here.

358
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:05,880
Where are you running to?

359
00:31:06,560 --> 00:31:08,680
We’re husband and wife.
Why can’t we sleep together?

360
00:31:08,760 --> 00:31:09,720
Huh?

361
00:31:10,400 --> 00:31:11,720
Do I have to transition
into a woman for you?

362
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:19,080
- Ing.
- Don't come any closer.

363
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:20,720
I'm your husband, IngIng.

364
00:31:21,480 --> 00:31:23,280
We're legally married.

365
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:26,480
Why can't I sleep with you?

366
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:28,200
But we agreed on this.

367
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:30,120
I agreed to marry you

368
00:31:32,040 --> 00:31:33,360
because I love you.

369
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:38,880
Wasn't it because
my dad agreed to write off your debt?

370
00:31:43,920 --> 00:31:44,880
Yeah.

371
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:47,720
Who says a husband
can't force himself on his wife?

372
00:31:49,040 --> 00:31:50,120
Don’t come any closer.

373
00:31:50,840 --> 00:31:52,200
If you touch me,

374
00:31:52,280 --> 00:31:53,520
I'll report you the police.

375
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:56,360
Report me?

376
00:31:57,960 --> 00:31:59,280
For what?

377
00:32:01,440 --> 00:32:02,960
Sexual assault.

378
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:07,600
If you can’t handle it,
just get a divorce.

379
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:09,240
What are you even saying?

380
00:32:11,480 --> 00:32:12,920
I won't divorce you.

381
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:24,160
IngIng.

382
00:32:26,120 --> 00:32:27,080
IngIng.

383
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:29,240
Let me come in and hold our son.

384
00:32:32,640 --> 00:32:33,680
IngIng.

385
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:36,320
Please open the door for me.

386
00:32:36,400 --> 00:32:37,760
I promise

387
00:32:38,280 --> 00:32:39,520
I won't do anything to him.

388
00:32:41,200 --> 00:32:42,040
Please, IngIng.

389
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:44,560
IngIng.

390
00:32:46,400 --> 00:32:48,240
IngIng, I'm his father too.

391
00:32:49,760 --> 00:32:51,080
Open the door for me.

392
00:32:55,160 --> 00:32:56,480
IngIng.

393
00:32:58,920 --> 00:32:59,840
IngIng.

394
00:33:00,920 --> 00:33:02,760
Can I hold our son?

395
00:33:05,720 --> 00:33:07,160
I'm sorry.

396
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:11,760
I came here just to see our son, really.

397
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,640
Please let me hold him.

398
00:33:17,440 --> 00:33:19,200
I won't do anything to him, IngIng.

399
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:23,200
I'm his father too.

400
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:28,520
Just think of it

401
00:33:29,480 --> 00:33:31,880
as me being his father for the last time.

402
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:35,440
I promise that if I get to hold Donut,

403
00:33:36,960 --> 00:33:40,320
I won't come back to this house
or show my face again.

404
00:33:41,080 --> 00:33:42,560
Please, IngIng.

405
00:33:43,680 --> 00:33:44,680
Please.

406
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:47,960
Please let me hold him.

407
00:33:57,480 --> 00:33:58,600
Donut.

408
00:33:58,680 --> 00:34:00,480
Wanna come to Daddy?

409
00:34:03,120 --> 00:34:04,240
Come to Daddy?

410
00:34:07,360 --> 00:34:08,360
Come on.

411
00:34:19,840 --> 00:34:20,840
Donut.

412
00:34:22,560 --> 00:34:23,679
Thank you.

413
00:34:27,960 --> 00:34:30,639
Shall we go downstairs and talk?

414
00:34:32,960 --> 00:34:34,239
Let's go together.

415
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:49,440
Let's go.

416
00:34:53,679 --> 00:34:55,199
- Open the door!
- IngIng.

417
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:57,800
If you still want to see your son,

418
00:34:58,320 --> 00:34:59,720
do as I say.

419
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:02,280
Or I’ll sue you for custody
and take him back.

420
00:35:02,360 --> 00:35:04,320
- Open the door!
- IngIng.

421
00:35:04,400 --> 00:35:06,040
Open the door! Give me back my son!

422
00:35:06,120 --> 00:35:07,280
Open the door!

423
00:35:07,360 --> 00:35:08,200
Listen to me.

424
00:35:10,160 --> 00:35:12,320
Don’t tell anyone about this

425
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:15,080
if you still want to see Donut.

426
00:35:15,600 --> 00:35:16,640
Do as I say.

427
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:18,480
No! Open the door!

428
00:35:18,560 --> 00:35:20,800
Open the door! Give him back!

429
00:35:20,880 --> 00:35:23,000
Give me back my son!

430
00:35:23,080 --> 00:35:24,440
Open the door.

431
00:35:24,520 --> 00:35:26,120
I’ll take Donut with me,

432
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:28,600
and you’ll never see him again.

433
00:35:29,360 --> 00:35:31,080
- No!
- Do as I tell you, IngIng.

434
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:32,480
Donut!

435
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:36,160
Don't do anything to him!

436
00:35:37,040 --> 00:35:38,280
Donut.

437
00:35:38,360 --> 00:35:40,240
Wait for me, okay?

438
00:35:40,320 --> 00:35:42,080
Just wait a little.

439
00:35:42,160 --> 00:35:43,920
I'll be right back.

440
00:35:53,800 --> 00:35:54,880
Ith.

441
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:56,520
- Ith.
- Sis.

442
00:35:56,600 --> 00:35:57,680
- Ith.
- Ing.

443
00:35:59,360 --> 00:36:00,200
Where's Donut?

444
00:36:00,800 --> 00:36:02,720
Donut’s upstairs with Guy.

445
00:36:02,800 --> 00:36:04,960
How could you leave Donut with him?

446
00:36:05,040 --> 00:36:06,640
He threatened me.

447
00:36:06,720 --> 00:36:09,280
He said if I don’t do as he says,

448
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:12,560
he'll sue me for full custody of Donut.

449
00:36:13,160 --> 00:36:14,360
That bastard.

450
00:36:14,960 --> 00:36:17,560
He told me not to tell anyone.

451
00:36:19,640 --> 00:36:21,440
What should I do?
I'm scared I'll lose Donut.

452
00:36:21,520 --> 00:36:22,880
What do we do, Ith?

453
00:36:25,440 --> 00:36:26,320
I'll help you.

454
00:36:30,960 --> 00:36:32,160
Come on.

455
00:36:45,520 --> 00:36:48,040
IngIng left all the messages on read.

456
00:36:48,120 --> 00:36:49,200
That's so strange.

457
00:36:49,280 --> 00:36:51,040
She's probably asleep.

458
00:36:54,160 --> 00:36:55,320
Where are you going, Ms. Lin?

459
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:57,520
I'm going to check if something happened.

460
00:36:58,120 --> 00:36:59,120
Then I'll go with you.

461
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:02,400
No need. Wait for me here,
so you can help if anything happens.

462
00:37:02,480 --> 00:37:04,840
Alright.
If you don’t call me in ten minutes,

463
00:37:04,920 --> 00:37:06,320
I'll call the police, okay?

464
00:37:33,080 --> 00:37:35,280
Oh? What brings you here?

465
00:37:35,800 --> 00:37:38,360
I was nearby for work,
so I thought I’d stop by.

466
00:37:38,440 --> 00:37:40,560
I called and texted you,

467
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:42,120
but you didn’t respond at all.

468
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:44,600
Oh.

469
00:37:45,240 --> 00:37:48,320
I must have been putting my son to sleep.

470
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:49,600
I'm sorry.

471
00:37:54,480 --> 00:37:56,000
Is Donut upstairs?

472
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:57,600
- Yes.
- Yes.

473
00:38:07,200 --> 00:38:08,080
You have a guest over?

474
00:38:08,160 --> 00:38:09,440
No.

475
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:11,960
It's my friend,

476
00:38:12,040 --> 00:38:12,880
sleeping upstairs.

477
00:38:16,000 --> 00:38:17,040
Oh.

478
00:38:18,480 --> 00:38:19,880
Then I won't disturb you.

479
00:38:19,960 --> 00:38:21,920
See you at Play Park tomorrow.

480
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:23,040
Yes.

481
00:38:23,560 --> 00:38:24,960
Drive home safely.

482
00:38:52,480 --> 00:38:54,160
Did you see IngIng's ex-husband?

483
00:38:54,240 --> 00:38:55,240
I didn't.

484
00:38:57,600 --> 00:38:58,640
But I feel something’s off.

485
00:38:58,720 --> 00:39:00,560
It’s like the two of them
were hiding something.

486
00:39:00,640 --> 00:39:03,160
She’s definitely hiding
her husband upstairs.

487
00:39:03,240 --> 00:39:05,440
It must be like I suspected, Ms. Lin.

488
00:39:05,520 --> 00:39:07,480
IngIng still hasn't divorced her husband,

489
00:39:07,560 --> 00:39:09,320
and now they're teaming up to scam you.

490
00:39:09,920 --> 00:39:11,680
She hasn't asked me for a single baht.

491
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:14,320
We even split the dinner bills.
How could she be scamming me?

492
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:18,480
Ms. Lin, this is the stage
where she gains your trust.

493
00:39:19,640 --> 00:39:21,280
Should we stay and watch?

494
00:39:21,920 --> 00:39:23,480
I remember her husband's face.

495
00:39:23,560 --> 00:39:25,320
We’ll find out the truth.

496
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:26,480
Let's go.

497
00:39:26,560 --> 00:39:27,680
I'm exhausted.

498
00:39:28,760 --> 00:39:29,960
Ms. Lin…

499
00:39:30,040 --> 00:39:31,880
You’re afraid of the truth, aren’t you?

500
00:39:31,960 --> 00:39:32,840
I'm not.

501
00:39:33,840 --> 00:39:36,240
Then please go home. I’ll stay and watch.

502
00:39:50,760 --> 00:39:51,880
Donut.

503
00:39:52,440 --> 00:39:53,760
Come to Mama.

504
00:39:55,160 --> 00:39:56,120
Donut.

505
00:39:56,200 --> 00:39:57,600
Come to Mama, okay?

506
00:39:59,600 --> 00:40:00,760
How’s it going?

507
00:40:02,200 --> 00:40:03,400
What?

508
00:40:04,520 --> 00:40:06,360
Afraid he'll get
too attached to his father?

509
00:40:06,960 --> 00:40:08,480
Say what you came to say.

510
00:40:08,560 --> 00:40:09,520
Ms. Lin has left.

511
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:11,160
Say it so you can leave too.

512
00:40:11,240 --> 00:40:13,360
In the divorce settlement,

513
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:16,160
I granted you custody.

514
00:40:17,120 --> 00:40:18,840
But I’m not prohibited from visiting him.

515
00:40:19,600 --> 00:40:21,400
I was stupid to overlook that.

516
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:25,760
Ing paid you to divorce her

517
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:27,480
using almost all our money.

518
00:40:28,000 --> 00:40:29,760
Wasn’t that enough?

519
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:37,320
How much more do you want?

520
00:40:43,160 --> 00:40:45,880
I'll agree to sign
an additional settlement

521
00:40:46,400 --> 00:40:48,800
never to see my son again

522
00:40:49,400 --> 00:40:52,440
and never let him know
that I’m his father.

523
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:54,160
Is that okay?

524
00:40:58,640 --> 00:40:59,600
How much?

525
00:41:00,200 --> 00:41:01,040
Ing.

526
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:03,800
Haven’t we paid him enough already?

527
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:07,000
Take Donut upstairs.

528
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:11,320
Let's go.

529
00:41:11,400 --> 00:41:12,720
Go with Uncle Ith.

530
00:41:13,240 --> 00:41:14,120
Go.

531
00:41:25,920 --> 00:41:27,360
You’re so quick to pay me, huh?

532
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:30,000
Your new girlfriend must be rich.

533
00:41:30,600 --> 00:41:31,680
Ms. Lin has nothing to do with this.

534
00:41:32,200 --> 00:41:33,720
I’ll get the money myself.

535
00:41:34,800 --> 00:41:35,880
How much do you want?

536
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:13,560
I'm her ex-husband.

537
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:15,840
Are you crazy?
My boss has never been married.

538
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:17,640
Is IngIng your boss?

539
00:42:18,360 --> 00:42:19,320
Hey.

540
00:42:21,280 --> 00:42:22,520
It's really him.

541
00:42:35,120 --> 00:42:36,440
Five hundred thousand?

542
00:42:37,720 --> 00:42:39,760
All our accounts combined
won’t even cover that.

543
00:42:40,920 --> 00:42:42,800
Where are you supposed to find
that kind of money?

544
00:42:43,400 --> 00:42:45,120
He said he'll give me a month.

545
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:46,480
That's not enough time.

546
00:42:47,520 --> 00:42:49,400
Worst case, I’ll sell the car.

547
00:42:49,480 --> 00:42:50,640
Ing.

548
00:42:51,720 --> 00:42:54,080
It’s worth it if it ends this.

549
00:42:54,600 --> 00:42:56,480
And how much can we trust him?

550
00:42:59,360 --> 00:43:01,520
If he doesn’t sign, we don’t pay him.

551
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:02,720
That’s fair, right?

552
00:43:04,120 --> 00:43:05,160
Should we tell Ms. Lin?

553
00:43:05,240 --> 00:43:06,360
No.

554
00:43:07,400 --> 00:43:09,120
Five hundred thousand
is just pocket change to her.

555
00:43:09,800 --> 00:43:11,720
Don't ever let Ms. Lin
find out about this.

556
00:43:18,880 --> 00:43:20,600
This is our family matter.

557
00:43:21,960 --> 00:43:23,360
I can handle it.

558
00:43:40,280 --> 00:43:42,040
<i>It’s him. I’m certain.</i>

559
00:43:42,120 --> 00:43:44,600
I remember IngIng's ex-husband clearly.

560
00:43:45,160 --> 00:43:46,920
They must be working together.

561
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:48,920
You’re being scammed, Ms. Lin.

562
00:43:56,920 --> 00:43:59,560
IngIng seems so busy with work
that she hasn’t had time to see me.

563
00:43:59,640 --> 00:44:01,680
<i>Do you have an urgent need for money?</i>

564
00:44:01,760 --> 00:44:03,280
<i>Ms. Lin, you have to stay firm.</i>

565
00:44:03,360 --> 00:44:05,600
<i>The evidence couldn't be clearer.</i>

566
00:44:05,680 --> 00:44:07,120
<i>They're tricking you.</i>

567
00:44:07,200 --> 00:44:09,440
<i>Since I started dating Ing,</i>

568
00:44:09,520 --> 00:44:11,280
<i>it’s felt like a dream, Jane.</i>

569
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:13,440
<i>I've been really happy.</i>

570
00:44:13,520 --> 00:44:15,120
How could a baby
just disappear like that, Ith?

571
00:44:15,200 --> 00:44:16,200
Or…

572
00:44:16,280 --> 00:44:18,240
could Donut have been kidnapped?

573
00:44:18,320 --> 00:44:20,360
<i>Did you order Play Park</i>
<i>to be shut down, Dad?</i>

574
00:44:20,440 --> 00:44:23,320
<i>You shouldn’t have interfered</i>
<i>with my responsibilities.</i>

575
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:25,160
<i>I feel betrayed.</i>

576
00:46:22,120 --> 00:46:26,840
Subtitle translation by: Anan Pratchayakul
